# Technical-debt suppression budget — total of #nosec + //nolint directives.
# A RATCHET: this number may only go DOWN. New suppressions must either be
# offset by removing an old one, or accompanied by a justified increase here
# (reviewed in the PR). Enforced by scripts/debt-guard.sh.
#
# When you remove suppressions, lower this number to lock the gain in.
#
# 2026-07: +1 for the raster continuous-value decode — sampleToFloat must call
# math.Float32frombits(uint32(raw)) to reinterpret a float32 band's bit pattern;
# the uint32 narrowing is intentional and unavoidable (gosec G115). Integer bands
# are decoded by masking (no suppression) and the tile/COG open shares one G304.
#
# 2026-07: +1 for the set-based batch query (geopackage/batch.go buildBatchPointQuery,
# gosec G201): the SQL interpolates the layer/geom identifiers (double-quoted) because
# SQLite cannot parameterize identifiers — the same justified pattern as
# executePointQuery. One suppression covers the whole query build.
27
